OL,3,CClawed hammers wielded by pupil were
OL,4,C'tools, not weapons', Blundell's head
OL,5,Csays
OL,7,FThe head of a private boarding school
OL,8,Fin Devon, where a pupil attacked two
OL,9,Fpeers and a housemaster with hammers,
OL,10,Fhas responded to his conviction at
OL,11,FExeter Crown Court.
OL,13,FA 17-year-old has been found guilty on
OL,14,Fthree counts of attempted murder in
OL,15,Fconnection to an incident at
OL,16,FBlundell's School in Tiverton.
OL,18,FThe school's head, Bart Wielenga,
OL,19,Fwrote a letter to the school community
OL,20,Ffollowing the verdict on Friday 21
OL,21,FJune.
