OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F436A1719065438
OL,3,CClawed hammers wielded by pupil were
OL,4,C'tools, not weapons', Blundell's head
OL,5,Csays
OL,7,F"I remain tremendously proud of our
OL,8,Fschool community and its response to
OL,9,Fcircumstances that have been
OL,10,Fprofoundly shocking and entirely
OL,11,Funprecedented.
OL,13,F"No school would ever wish something
OL,14,Flike this, but the conduct of pupils,
OL,15,Fstaff, parents and the wider
OL,16,FBlundell's community throughout the
OL,17,Fpast year has only been encouraging
OL,18,Fand reassuring. We have much to be
OL,19,Fgrateful for.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/8
