OL,3,CClawed hammers wielded by pupil were
OL,4,C'tools, not weapons', Blundell's head
OL,5,Csays
OL,7,F"You may have read the press reports
OL,8,Fon the trial referring to weapons and
OL,9,Flocked drawers.
OL,11,F"I want to reiterate that they were
OL,12,Ftools and not weapons (many items
OL,13,Fcould be used as weapons) and that
OL,14,Flocked drawers are part of the
OL,15,F'National Minimum Standards that
OL,16,Fboarding schools must meet in order to
OL,17,Fsafeguard and protect children in
OL,18,Ftheir care'.
OL,20,F"It is a regulatory requirement to
OL,21,Fgive pupils a lockable facility.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/8
