OL,3,CClawed hammers wielded by pupil were
OL,4,C'tools, not weapons', Blundell's head
OL,5,Csays
OL,7,F"I have stressed to pupils in numerous
OL,8,Fassemblies over the past year that
OL,9,Fthis incident is not something that we
OL,10,Fare ashamed of. It is part of our
OL,11,Fshared story. Difficult things happen
OL,12,Fin life, and we want to teach young
OL,13,Fpeople that we can talk openly about
OL,14,Four fears and anxieties as they relate
OL,15,Fto difficult events in life.
OL,17,F"We will continue to foster a
OL,18,Fsensitive, balanced, honest, and
OL,19,Fcourageous response to this tragic
OL,20,Fevent. Yours faithfully, Bart
OL,21,FWielenga."
